{"questionId":"11671","questionHtml":"<p>A student is verifying the equation</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage mjpage__block\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\" alttext=\"x = \\frac{{2\\lambda Y}}{z}\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>λ</mi>\n      <mi>Y</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>z</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The percentage uncertainties are:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/3fb0624e256a9dc541948ab71bbc21b4aee854ef.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">What is the percentage uncertainty in x?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">A. 5 %</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">B. 15 %</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">C. 25 %</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">D. 30 %</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"11671","referenceCode":"19M.1.HL.TZ1.1","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A student is verifying the equation x = 2 λ Y z The percentage uncertainties are: What is the percentage uncertainty in x? A. 5 % B. 15 % C. 25 % D. 30 %","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"1","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","1.2 – Uncertainties and errors","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}